[https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Advanced+Searching#AdvancedSearching-LESSTHANEQUALS:<=]

The way this behaviour works is if you specify the date such as the below, it won't pick up the current day. For example, if I want to search for all issues that were updated before and also including 30/01/13:

{noformat}
updated <= 2013-01-30
{noformat}

However, this will not pick up any issues updated on 30/01/13 because it's searching for the date "2013-01-30 00:00:01". So it can pick up issues on that day, we would need to increase the date, for example:

{noformat}
updated <= 2013-01-31
{noformat}

I'm not sure of the best way to explain this in the docs - can you please add this in using your magical touch? If you could please put it in the last two major versions as well that would be ideal (JIRA050, JIRA051, JIRA052).

THANKS :)

